{{Cocos-stub}}

{{Orphan|date=May 2011}}

'''Lichte Trough''' ({{coord|76|25|S|30|0|W|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is an undersea trough named for Professor [[Heinrich Lichte]] (1910–1988), a [[geodesist]] who specialized in [[glaciology]]. The name was proposed by Dr. [[Heinrich Hinze]] of the [[Alfred Wegener Institute for Polar and Marine Research]], [[Bremerhaven]], Germany, and was approved by the [[Advisory Committee for Undersea Features]] in June 1997.<ref name=gnis/>

