The following is a complete '''list of films''' produced and/or distributed by American production and distribution company '''[[Dimension Films]]''', a subsidiary of [[The Weinstein Company]], formerly owned by [[Walt Disney Studios (division)|The Walt Disney Company]] under [[Miramax]]. Dimension Films began in 1992, and has produced and distributed numerous genre films, largely [[horror film|horror]], [[science fiction film|sci-fi]], and action films.<ref>{{cite book|author=Plunkett, Jack W.|publisher=Plunkett Research, Ltd.|year=2007|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yPLb0cA8Gv0C&pg=PT400&dq=dimension+films+titles&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwio0t_0ycvWAhUQ-GMKHRnzDQIQ6AEIKDAA#v=onepage&q=dimension%20films%20titles&f=false|title=Plunkett's Entertainment and Media Industry Almanac: The Only Comprehensive Guide to the Entertainment and Media Industry|isbn= 978-1-593-92066-1}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=American Independent Cinema|page=44|author=King, Geoff|year=2005|publisher=I.B.Tauris|isbn= 978-1-850-43938-7}}</ref> The company has owned the rights to, as well as produced and distributed, the films of several horror franchises, including the ''[[Scream (franchise)|Scream]]'' films, the ''[[Children of the Corn (film series)|Children of the Corn]]'' series, ''[[Hellraiser (franchise)|Hellraiser]]'' series, and the ''[[Halloween (franchise)|Halloween]]'' films, among others.
In addition to distributing films for theatrical release, Dimension Films also released numerous titles [[direct-to-video]]. In 2008, the company introduced the ''[[Dimension Films#Dimension Extreme|Dimension Extreme]]'' division, a [[DVD]] label for "extreme" cinema, which mainly consisted of domestic and international horror titles.
